A two-year-old boy is recovering after falling into a cheetah exhibit at the Cleveland Metroparks Zoo after his parents dangled him over the edge .
The toddler 's mother was holding him and another child when he slipped and fell between 10 to 12ft and into the pit on Saturday around 3 pm .
The child was rescued by his parents before firefighters and paramedics arrived on the scene .
The boy 's leg was injured in the fall , but he was not attacked by the animals .